1
00:00:00,710 --> 00:00:03,740
(Ma)

2
00:00:10,180 --> 00:00:13,450
Oh my gosh, what do we do?

3
00:00:14,520 --> 00:00:15,950
Oh my goodness.

4
00:00:21,360 --> 00:00:23,090
Chae Hwa Young.

5
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:28,030
What in the world...

6
00:00:29,570 --> 00:00:31,800
was she trying to pull?

7
00:00:33,540 --> 00:00:35,810
What happened? Mom, was that you?

8
00:00:36,010 --> 00:00:38,340
So it was grapefruit juice,
not pomegranate?

9
00:00:38,610 --> 00:00:42,350
Yes. In any case,
I'm just glad everything's okay.

10
00:00:42,680 --> 00:00:45,320
If we had fallen for
Chae Hwa Young's trap,

11
00:00:45,450 --> 00:00:49,750
the Chairman would've gone
to the hospital instead of her.

12
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:54,060
How could Chae Hwa Young go that far
just to take down Grandfather?

13
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:00,370
Shouldn't you be resting
at the hospital for a day?

14
00:01:01,900 --> 00:01:04,100
With Oh Jang Mi and Jung Suk Hee
still in the house,

15
00:01:04,570 --> 00:01:06,270
how can I possibly rest?

16
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:09,540
Are you feeling any better now?

17
00:01:09,970 --> 00:01:13,340
Yes, it's easier to breathe.

18
00:01:14,050 --> 00:01:15,310
That was a close call.

19
00:01:15,350 --> 00:01:16,980
But now that I've gone and proved...

20
00:01:16,980 --> 00:01:19,750
there was grapefruit in the concentrate,

21
00:01:20,550 --> 00:01:22,090
how am I supposed to cover that up?

22
00:01:22,250 --> 00:01:23,920
Yeom San Wol was the one who bought it.

23
00:01:24,660 --> 00:01:27,360
Only you, me,
and Jung Suk Hee know the fact...

24
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:29,130
that the cap was already open, right?

25
00:01:29,730 --> 00:01:32,300
And that grapefruit concentrate
was mixed in the juice.

26
00:01:32,900 --> 00:01:35,770
On top of that, you drank it
without knowing what was in it.

27
00:01:37,570 --> 00:01:38,700
You're right.

28
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:40,440
This should do it.

29
00:01:41,210 --> 00:01:42,210
What do you mean?

30
00:01:43,210 --> 00:01:45,510
This isn't something
we can just let slide.

31
00:01:45,640 --> 00:01:48,580
CEO Chae knows full well
you're taking blood pressure medication.

32
00:01:48,710 --> 00:01:51,620
How could she try to make you drink juice
with grapefruit extract?

33
00:01:51,920 --> 00:01:53,490
You could have gone into shock.

34
00:01:53,950 --> 00:01:56,120
Chae Hwa Young did this on purpose.

35
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:58,090
If something had happened to you,

36
00:01:58,490 --> 00:02:00,530
she would've framed my mom for it.

37
00:02:00,730 --> 00:02:03,860
This is unacceptable.
I should teach Chae Hwa Young a lesson.

38
00:02:04,300 --> 00:02:07,530
She might have even made me buy this
on purpose.

39
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:11,600
Grandfather's fine. He's perfectly okay.

40
00:02:11,700 --> 00:02:13,040
We're lucky you got confused...

41
00:02:13,040 --> 00:02:15,770
and switched Grandfather's glass
with CEO Chae's,

42
00:02:16,070 --> 00:02:19,280
- or this could have been a huge disaster.
- That's right.

43
00:02:19,380 --> 00:02:20,950
And it's also strange...

44
00:02:20,950 --> 00:02:23,080
that grapefruit concentrate was mixed in
with the pomegranate.

45
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:25,350
We have to get to the bottom of this.

46
00:02:28,650 --> 00:02:29,650
You.

47
00:02:30,260 --> 00:02:31,520
Come sit here.

48
00:02:32,820 --> 00:02:33,830
Yes.

49
00:02:41,370 --> 00:02:44,640
Were you deliberately trying
to make me collapse...

50
00:02:44,870 --> 00:02:47,240
by mixing grapefruit extract
into the juice?

51
00:02:47,640 --> 00:02:48,640
Were you...

52
00:02:49,740 --> 00:02:51,480
trying to kill me?

53
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:52,510
Father.

54
00:02:52,910 --> 00:02:55,910
How can you say something so awful?
That's absurd.

55
00:02:56,050 --> 00:02:58,180
Then how do you explain what happened?

56
00:02:59,020 --> 00:03:00,690
That's what I'd like to ask you, Father.

57
00:03:02,050 --> 00:03:03,120
Jung Suk Hee.

58
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:04,760
What happened?

59
00:03:05,260 --> 00:03:07,390
I know for a fact
I only bought pomegranate extract.

60
00:03:07,790 --> 00:03:10,930
So why was there grapefruit extract
mixed into the juice I drank?

61
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:12,430
What are you trying to say?

62
00:03:13,230 --> 00:03:14,670
Are you saying my mom deliberately...

63
00:03:14,900 --> 00:03:17,940
spiked the juice you were drinking
with grapefruit extract?

64
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:20,070
How else do you explain it?

65
00:03:21,040 --> 00:03:24,640
I specifically told Yeom San Wol
to only buy pomegranate extract.

66
00:03:25,340 --> 00:03:26,340
Isn't that right, Yeom San Wol?

67
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:28,950
Yes, that's right.

68
00:03:29,010 --> 00:03:31,150
And then all I did was show...

69
00:03:31,450 --> 00:03:34,050
Jung Suk Hee how to make the juice
and leave.

70
00:03:34,650 --> 00:03:37,990
Why would I add grapefruit extract
unless I was out of my mind?

71
00:03:38,060 --> 00:03:40,020
You're the one who put
the grapefruit extract in it...

72
00:03:40,390 --> 00:03:42,990
and then told my mom
to serve it to Grandfather!

73
00:03:43,060 --> 00:03:45,600
That's absurd.
Stop making up stories, Oh Jang Mi.

74
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:47,530
If I had done that,

75
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,900
it would've been obvious right away
that it was me.

76
00:03:49,970 --> 00:03:52,370
You really think
I'd do something that foolish?

77
00:03:52,540 --> 00:03:55,310
Now that she mentions it, she has a point.

78
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:57,940
My own body is proof
that's not true, isn't it?

79
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:01,310
You saw me collapse earlier, Father.

80
00:04:02,080 --> 00:04:06,180
Unless I have a death wish,
why would I do such a thing?

81
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:09,450
Look at her, desperately squirming
her way out of this.

82
00:04:10,020 --> 00:04:12,820
How do I prove that
Chae Hwa Young was behind it?

83
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:15,660
Jung Suk Hee, tell the truth.

84
00:04:16,030 --> 00:04:18,060
Why did you put grapefruit extract
in the juice?

85
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:20,430
You know I'm allergic to grapefruit,
don't you?

86
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:23,770
- That's why you tried to kill me.
- Chae Hwa Young,

87
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:27,640
why are you pinning this on my mother?
Stop talking nonsense.

88
00:04:27,710 --> 00:04:30,380
I remember exactly what Jung Suk Hee
said at the funeral.

89
00:04:30,740 --> 00:04:33,080
I swear I will rip you to shreds.

90
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:36,910
I'll rip your organs out one by one...

91
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:41,220
and make you die in agony, Chae Hwa Young!

92
00:04:44,290 --> 00:04:45,560
Jung Suk Hee,

93
00:04:46,060 --> 00:04:49,660
you suspected I killed Seo Rin.
That's why you tried to kill me.

94
00:04:50,090 --> 00:04:51,130
That's not true.

95
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:55,430
The thief, Chae Hwa Young, made me do it.
It wasn't my fault.

96
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:57,340
Then why was there grapefruit
in the pomegranate juice?

97
00:04:57,640 --> 00:05:01,840
Even with your intellectual disability,
you're an expert when it comes to food.

98
00:05:02,140 --> 00:05:06,410
Father, she knew what she was doing.
I'm telling you, she tried to kill me.

99
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:08,610
- That's enough!
- Father, I've been wronged!

100
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:11,320
I almost died!

101
00:05:11,680 --> 00:05:13,520
Please ban Jung Suk Hee from this house.

102
00:05:13,850 --> 00:05:18,460
Who knows when she might try
to kill me again?

103
00:05:18,460 --> 00:05:20,830
Chae Hwa Young,
you've really gone too far.

104
00:05:21,290 --> 00:05:23,490
Are you really trying to frame
my mother for what you did?

105
00:05:24,060 --> 00:05:25,060
Fine.

106
00:05:25,330 --> 00:05:29,230
Then how about we find out where that
grapefruit extract was purchased?

107
00:05:29,530 --> 00:05:32,340
Since Yeom San Wol said she only bought
the pomegranate extract,

108
00:05:32,540 --> 00:05:35,510
that means you must have bought
the grapefruit extract separately.

109
00:05:35,570 --> 00:05:38,910
Who says I'm the one who bought it?
How dare you try to pin this on me?

110
00:05:39,580 --> 00:05:41,780
Doesn't your half-wit mother
hold a grudge against me...

111
00:05:41,780 --> 00:05:43,410
for losing her own daughter?

112
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:46,620
And that gives you the right to frame
my mother for your crime?

113
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:49,490
Chae Hwa Young gave me the bottle.
She made a separate one for Grandfather.

114
00:05:49,990 --> 00:05:52,960
- Suk Hee did nothing wrong.
- Jung Suk Hee, stop lying!

115
00:05:53,660 --> 00:05:55,690
If I made a separate one
for Father as you claim,

116
00:05:55,960 --> 00:05:57,830
then why am I the one who drank
the grapefruit juice?

117
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:01,930
You knew I was allergic,
and you fed it to me on purpose.

118
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:03,400
That's not true.

119
00:06:03,670 --> 00:06:06,140
- That thief is lying.
- All right.

120
00:06:06,470 --> 00:06:10,040
Since you were also a victim,
I'll let it slide this time.

121
00:06:10,540 --> 00:06:12,280
But from now on,
whenever you bring something,

122
00:06:12,810 --> 00:06:14,180
you need to be extremely careful.

123
00:06:14,180 --> 00:06:16,180
Certain food combinations...

124
00:06:16,380 --> 00:06:19,350
can be a matter of life and death.

125
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:20,820
Thank you, Father.

126
00:06:21,620 --> 00:06:23,350
Thank you for believing me.

127
00:06:24,020 --> 00:06:25,620
I'll be more careful from now on.

128
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:37,700
That was too close.
I almost died because of her.

129
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:40,170
I have to get her thrown out.
This can't go on.

130
00:06:40,670 --> 00:06:42,510
As long as Jung Suk Hee is in this house,

131
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:44,910
I can't let my guard down
for a single moment.

132
00:06:48,380 --> 00:06:50,920
Mom, don't be so upset.

133
00:06:51,250 --> 00:06:52,820
I never thought that monster,

134
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:54,490
Chae Hwa Young, would get away
with it like that.

135
00:06:54,650 --> 00:06:58,160
This isn't working.
From now on, whenever she pulls something,

136
00:06:58,520 --> 00:07:00,590
we have to make sure to get it on camera.

137
00:07:00,930 --> 00:07:01,930
Let's do that, Mom.

138
00:07:02,460 --> 00:07:06,530
But you still have to be careful, Mom.
Chae Hwa Young is absolutely furious now.

139
00:07:06,830 --> 00:07:09,900
Okay, I will. You be careful too, Jang Mi.

140
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:12,040
Okay.

141
00:07:17,740 --> 00:07:18,810
Chae Hwa Young...

142
00:07:19,510 --> 00:07:20,880
is tougher than I thought.

143
00:07:30,690 --> 00:07:31,720
Hand that over for a second.

144
00:07:32,020 --> 00:07:34,230
Why? This is the Chairman's cutlery.

145
00:07:34,230 --> 00:07:35,660
Of course I know that.

146
00:07:38,700 --> 00:07:41,800
I've been wondering about this
for the longest time.

147
00:07:42,470 --> 00:07:45,000
What on earth does this crest mean?

148
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:48,040
Why are you getting your fingerprints
all over something I just polished?

149
00:07:48,110 --> 00:07:50,340
Relax. You can just polish it again.

150
00:07:50,580 --> 00:07:53,280
What's with the attitude, Geum Soon?
It's not like you do much around here.

151
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:54,910
I'll explain, so listen closely.

152
00:07:56,380 --> 00:07:58,580
For a long time now,

153
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:01,520
this crest has been engraved
on the Chairman's important possessions.

154
00:08:01,950 --> 00:08:03,150
Come to think of it,

155
00:08:03,350 --> 00:08:06,820
I've seen this symbol
in the Chairman's study before.

156
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:08,260
Look here.

157
00:08:08,660 --> 00:08:10,160
It's on Seo Rin's silverware, too.

158
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:12,960
On Seo Rin's? Oh my goodness!

159
00:08:13,700 --> 00:08:14,700
You're right.

160
00:08:15,330 --> 00:08:20,300
This is purely reserved
for the Chairman's bloodline.

161
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:23,980
Anyway, it could be the family's crest.

162
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:27,140
Then if I just legally marry the Chairman,

163
00:08:27,450 --> 00:08:30,450
will I get to eat with a golden spoon
engraved with this symbol?

164
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:33,520
And Hong Ju, too?
Oh my gosh! I can't believe it!

165
00:08:35,850 --> 00:08:39,090
Good grief.
Yeom San Wol still hasn't given up.

166
00:08:39,220 --> 00:08:40,220
Unbelievable.

167
00:08:50,470 --> 00:08:51,840
(Hills Hotel Acquisition Proposal)

168
00:08:52,670 --> 00:08:53,840
Hills Hotel?

169
00:08:56,940 --> 00:08:58,240
(Company Overview,
Construction Project Outline)

170
00:08:58,340 --> 00:09:00,010
Is Dream acquiring Hills?

171
00:09:01,450 --> 00:09:02,910
This is the first I've heard about this.

172
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:16,260
You weren't in, so I was just dropping off
these documents for your approval.

173
00:09:17,090 --> 00:09:18,100
Really?

174
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:22,070
Are you free this evening?
I have a private matter to discuss.

175
00:09:22,230 --> 00:09:25,240
If it's personal and not work-related,
I'm not interested.

176
00:09:27,610 --> 00:09:28,610
Director Ma.

177
00:09:32,380 --> 00:09:34,450
So you're just never going to
call me Jang Mi?

178
00:09:35,150 --> 00:09:37,450
You're no longer the late Oh Jang Mi.

179
00:09:38,350 --> 00:09:40,180
You're my fiancee, Ma Seo Rin.

180
00:09:41,050 --> 00:09:42,990
I should congratulate you
on finally finding your rightful place.

181
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,860
You're truly despicable.

182
00:09:46,220 --> 00:09:47,260
Is Kang Baek Ho all right?

183
00:09:47,730 --> 00:09:48,730
Baek Ho? Why?

184
00:09:49,390 --> 00:09:50,460
What are you talking about?

185
00:09:50,930 --> 00:09:53,730
So I guess Baek Ho
hasn't told you anything yet.

186
00:09:54,170 --> 00:09:55,630
Did something happen to Baek Ho?

187
00:10:01,970 --> 00:10:04,510
Team Leader Jin,
how's the industry looking these days?

188
00:10:05,110 --> 00:10:07,040
Our hotel is still in the red,

189
00:10:07,650 --> 00:10:09,950
so I imagine our competitors are
in bad shape too, right?

190
00:10:10,210 --> 00:10:11,920
Everyone's got their own fires to put out.

191
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:15,990
I hear the Hills Group in particular
is in complete shambles.

192
00:10:16,220 --> 00:10:17,220
Hills Hotel?

193
00:10:18,020 --> 00:10:19,490
But that's a pretty big hotel, though.

194
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:23,030
It's big on the outside,
but I hear it's rotten inside with debt.

195
00:10:23,330 --> 00:10:25,400
Apparently, they overextended themselves
with their recent expansion,

196
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:27,570
and rumor has it
they got seriously burned.

197
00:10:27,970 --> 00:10:31,940
So because of their financial troubles,
they might even sell off Hills Hotel.

198
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,200
No way.

199
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:36,910
But the Hills Hotel is the group's icon
and its main cash cow.

200
00:10:37,210 --> 00:10:38,810
There's no way they'd sell it.

201
00:10:39,380 --> 00:10:40,640
They'd sell off something else first.

202
00:10:42,580 --> 00:10:43,580
No.

203
00:10:43,980 --> 00:10:45,980
That proposal
Kang Jun Ho was looking at...

204
00:10:46,450 --> 00:10:48,350
wasn't just a simple analysis
of industry trends.

205
00:10:49,220 --> 00:10:51,220
It means a specific plan
has been set in motion.

206
00:10:57,700 --> 00:10:59,730
Baek Ho, we need to talk urgently.

207
00:11:00,330 --> 00:11:02,200
Wait, they're acquiring Hills Hotel?

208
00:11:02,670 --> 00:11:04,400
You're saying CEO Chae
and General Manager Kang...

209
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:05,640
are secretly pushing for it?

210
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:08,410
Keep your voice down.
Someone might hear us.

211
00:11:08,670 --> 00:11:09,870
How did you find out?

212
00:11:10,110 --> 00:11:12,310
I happened to see it
on General Manager Kang's desk.

213
00:11:12,810 --> 00:11:16,310
Chae Hwa Young is acquiring the hotel
behind Grandfather's back...

214
00:11:16,650 --> 00:11:19,680
as part of a scheme
to completely take over Dream Group.

215
00:11:20,150 --> 00:11:24,060
They'd need hundreds of billions
to acquire Hills Hotel.

216
00:11:24,190 --> 00:11:26,860
Even with loans,
that would be nowhere near enough.

217
00:11:27,060 --> 00:11:29,960
Investors.
They're probably looking for investors.

218
00:11:30,330 --> 00:11:33,000
Plus, she must have a huge slush fund
she scraped together.

219
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:35,430
A slush fund is black money.
It's completely off the books.

220
00:11:35,770 --> 00:11:39,270
If they use it carelessly,
they'll be caught in a fund investigation.

221
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:44,140
She'll need a front to launder the money
and make it look legitimate.

222
00:11:44,280 --> 00:11:48,380
What kind of insane investor would launder
Chae Hwa Young's dirty money...

223
00:11:48,380 --> 00:11:50,680
and be willing to pick a fight
with Dream Group?

224
00:11:50,850 --> 00:11:55,090
That's why Chae Hwa Young must be
desperately searching for one.

225
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:57,490
First, let's gather some intel.

226
00:12:02,260 --> 00:12:04,600
Are they even looking for investors
or not?

227
00:12:11,140 --> 00:12:13,970
Manager Lee, are you making any progress
finding an investor?

228
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:18,240
Are you or aren't you?
Just find someone already!

229
00:12:18,580 --> 00:12:20,380
Kang Hyuk, please eat before it gets cold.

230
00:12:24,550 --> 00:12:25,750
Wait, don't tell me...

231
00:12:25,950 --> 00:12:27,590
you are with Lawyer Han Young Ja
right now.

232
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:31,690
Please, eat. We work to live, right?

233
00:12:32,920 --> 00:12:34,960
Yes, I'll be there shortly.

234
00:12:35,290 --> 00:12:36,390
Hey, Lee Kang Hyuk!

235
00:12:40,660 --> 00:12:43,830
Don't get the wrong idea.
I just didn't want to eat alone.

236
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:47,540
It's been a while
since I had a home-cooked meal.

237
00:12:48,640 --> 00:12:52,540
So this is what my Jun Ho grew up eating.

238
00:12:52,940 --> 00:12:55,380
The housekeeper made everything.

239
00:12:56,550 --> 00:12:58,550
I'm not much of a cook.

240
00:12:58,820 --> 00:13:01,390
It wouldn't be fair
if you were good at everything.

241
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:08,760
It's delicious.

242
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:12,230
- Is it seasoned okay?
- Yes, it's perfect.

243
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:14,600
Not too bland, and not too salty.

244
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:22,510
Look at this.

245
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:24,340
What do you think you two are doing?

246
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:28,150
Are you flaunting your affair
right here in my house?

247
00:13:29,550 --> 00:13:31,050
How crude.

248
00:13:31,580 --> 00:13:33,380
Is that any way for a professor to speak?

249
00:13:34,490 --> 00:13:37,020
You've got no class.

250
00:13:37,020 --> 00:13:38,020
"Class?"

251
00:13:39,820 --> 00:13:41,730
Please. Aren't professors human?

252
00:13:41,730 --> 00:13:45,360
Are they supposed to still act all refined
after seeing this?

253
00:13:45,760 --> 00:13:48,670
Did you have to invite another man
into our home...

254
00:13:48,930 --> 00:13:50,900
and even cook a meal for him?

255
00:13:51,140 --> 00:13:54,370
Let me just repeat
what you always say to me.

256
00:13:54,840 --> 00:13:57,440
Please, try to have a little dignity.

257
00:13:58,140 --> 00:13:59,780
I can't believe this woman.

258
00:14:03,380 --> 00:14:04,380
Fine.

259
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:08,450
Yes, Hwa Young.

260
00:14:08,950 --> 00:14:12,190
I need you to come over
to my house right now.

261
00:14:12,520 --> 00:14:15,730
There's something you've just got to see.

262
00:14:15,990 --> 00:14:17,190
Come quickly.

263
00:14:34,910 --> 00:14:35,910
Look at this.

264
00:14:36,210 --> 00:14:39,950
She won't give me a divorce
but invites another man for a meal.

265
00:14:40,350 --> 00:14:42,550
It's like she's doing it just to spite me.

266
00:14:42,820 --> 00:14:46,520
I'm too embarrassed
to even tell anyone else about this.

267
00:14:47,290 --> 00:14:50,960
- It's so humiliating.
- Manager Lee, what are you doing here?

268
00:14:51,700 --> 00:14:52,700
I was just...

269
00:14:53,430 --> 00:14:54,700
having a meal.

270
00:14:56,100 --> 00:14:58,600
Han Young Ja, that's enough.

271
00:14:59,100 --> 00:15:00,540
You've gone too far.

272
00:15:00,670 --> 00:15:02,410
Is it a crime to have a meal now?

273
00:15:03,470 --> 00:15:07,410
Did we embrace,
like you and Kang Nam Bong do?

274
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:09,410
Did we whisper sweet nothings
to each other?

275
00:15:10,010 --> 00:15:12,580
All we did was share a meal.

276
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:16,020
Wait, we're having tea, too.

277
00:15:16,850 --> 00:15:20,790
I guess when your own hands are dirty,
you assume everyone else's are too.

278
00:15:22,490 --> 00:15:23,490
There's no point to this.

279
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:25,100
I should go.

280
00:15:30,470 --> 00:15:31,470
Han Young Ja.

281
00:15:32,170 --> 00:15:34,970
If you keep this up, I'll have to
take matters into my own hands.

282
00:15:35,340 --> 00:15:37,140
Stop harassing my assistant.

283
00:15:44,620 --> 00:15:47,050
So what
if she takes matters into her own hands?

284
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:49,750
She's the one with more to lose, not me.

285
00:15:50,620 --> 00:15:51,690
Isn't that right, Kang Nam Bong?

286
00:15:52,190 --> 00:15:54,060
Please, just stop.

287
00:15:54,530 --> 00:15:57,960
I guess this is your idea of getting even.

288
00:15:58,560 --> 00:16:02,100
But you're taking this way further
than I ever did.

289
00:16:05,740 --> 00:16:08,440
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

290
00:16:13,510 --> 00:16:15,410
Director Ma,
aren't you leaving for the day?

291
00:16:16,650 --> 00:16:17,720
I will in a bit.

292
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:21,050
Then I'll head out first.

293
00:16:21,650 --> 00:16:24,760
Sir. I'll leave you to speak
with Director Ma.

294
00:16:30,730 --> 00:16:32,230
If you have something to say,
get on with it.

295
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:34,200
I need to talk to you about Baek Ho.

296
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:37,570
Whatever it is about Baek Ho,
I'll hear it from him myself.

297
00:16:38,470 --> 00:16:40,700
The fact that he still hasn't told you...

298
00:16:40,700 --> 00:16:43,140
probably means
it's not an easy thing to say.

299
00:16:43,810 --> 00:16:46,010
- Don't you want to know?
- I don't want to know.

300
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:48,580
So, Kang Jun Ho, just stay out of it.

301
00:16:57,890 --> 00:16:59,020
What's this?

302
00:17:01,860 --> 00:17:03,060
But what's this here?

303
00:17:03,590 --> 00:17:07,230
- It looks like some kind of crest.
- I don't know what that is either.

304
00:17:07,630 --> 00:17:11,300
The person who left you at the orphanage
included it with you.

305
00:17:11,370 --> 00:17:15,510
It probably has something to do
with your family roots.

306
00:17:15,810 --> 00:17:19,080
Judging by this, I must have come
from a super rich family.

307
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:24,210
But if I was from a rich family,
why was I sent to an orphanage?

308
00:17:27,080 --> 00:17:28,620
Where did I come from?

309
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:31,160
Whose son am I?

310
00:17:37,330 --> 00:17:38,400
Yes, Chairman.

311
00:17:38,960 --> 00:17:40,600
(Missing Child,
Park Young Mi, Female, Age 55)

312
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:42,230
(Lost wearing a broken-heart necklace)

313
00:17:42,230 --> 00:17:43,770
(For anyone who helps find her,
a 50,000-dollar cash reward is offered.)

314
00:17:49,010 --> 00:17:51,380
Lawyer Kang, what do you think?

315
00:17:51,810 --> 00:17:55,480
Do you think this is enough
to find our Eun Hye?

316
00:17:55,750 --> 00:17:56,980
I notice that on the flyer,

317
00:17:57,410 --> 00:18:00,620
you left out any specific evidence
or features...

318
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:02,650
that would positively identify
your daughter.

319
00:18:03,020 --> 00:18:04,020
That was a good call.

320
00:18:04,860 --> 00:18:07,990
Of course.
I'm the only one who should know that.

321
00:18:09,530 --> 00:18:10,860
At the bottom of the flyer,

322
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:13,630
I think we should add a warning...

323
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:15,570
that any false reports
or fraudulent claims...

324
00:18:15,570 --> 00:18:17,500
will be strictly prosecuted...

325
00:18:17,570 --> 00:18:19,370
for fraud and obstruction of business.

326
00:18:20,070 --> 00:18:22,970
Yes, let's do as you say.

327
00:18:23,310 --> 00:18:25,110
We'll have the tip line go
to my secretary's office...

328
00:18:25,110 --> 00:18:28,610
No, Jang Mi and I will
handle all the tips ourselves.

329
00:18:29,380 --> 00:18:30,780
Why bother
when we have my secretarial staff?

330
00:18:30,980 --> 00:18:35,120
There might be people on the inside
trying to keep you in the dark.

331
00:18:35,620 --> 00:18:37,220
To prevent any information
from getting out,

332
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:41,960
we will transparently manage the process,
from fact-checking to DNA testing.

333
00:18:43,590 --> 00:18:44,930
All right, let's do that.

334
00:18:50,070 --> 00:18:51,600
And one more thing.

335
00:18:51,940 --> 00:18:55,010
You should take my Jang Mi out
for a meal soon.

336
00:18:55,940 --> 00:18:59,010
- A meal?
- You need to hurry up and marry her.

337
00:18:59,310 --> 00:19:02,110
After losing Seo Rin the way I did,

338
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:05,750
I feel like a part of my heart
has crumbled away.

339
00:19:07,150 --> 00:19:08,290
The void left by one person...

340
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:11,120
must be filled by someone new,
don't you think?

341
00:19:12,260 --> 00:19:13,920
Thank you, Chairman.

342
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:22,730
Still here?

343
00:19:23,730 --> 00:19:25,570
This worked out great.
Let's grab something to drink.

344
00:19:30,470 --> 00:19:31,480
Drink up.

345
00:19:31,710 --> 00:19:32,780
(Grapefruit Juice)

346
00:19:34,280 --> 00:19:36,150
Did you give this to me on purpose?

347
00:19:37,180 --> 00:19:39,420
- What?
- You forgot I'm allergic to grapefruit?

348
00:19:42,390 --> 00:19:43,620
Right.

349
00:19:43,750 --> 00:19:45,520
I guess we've grown so distant lately...

350
00:19:45,590 --> 00:19:47,490
that I even forgot you were
allergic to grapefruit.

351
00:19:53,330 --> 00:19:54,330
For the longest time,

352
00:19:54,930 --> 00:19:57,630
I thought you were
our parents' biological son.

353
00:19:58,300 --> 00:20:00,400
That's why I spent our entire childhood
envying you,

354
00:20:00,770 --> 00:20:02,640
and I was always so jealous of you.

355
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:04,140
That was just your own insecurity.

356
00:20:04,780 --> 00:20:07,540
Our parents never played favorites.

357
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:09,880
No, if anything,
since you were the one pulling away,

358
00:20:10,210 --> 00:20:11,450
they paid even more attention to you.

359
00:20:12,820 --> 00:20:14,080
That's what you think.

360
00:20:15,490 --> 00:20:17,790
But you can't deny
they were more comfortable around you.

361
00:20:17,850 --> 00:20:20,790
That's because you were never comfortable
with them in the first place.

362
00:20:21,490 --> 00:20:24,700
- They walked on eggshells around you.
- Enough.

363
00:20:25,830 --> 00:20:26,860
I'll give you this.

364
00:20:28,030 --> 00:20:31,230
I was always insecure
about whose child I really was,

365
00:20:31,300 --> 00:20:32,770
so I couldn't be confident around you.

366
00:20:34,340 --> 00:20:35,770
But now the tables have turned.

367
00:20:37,270 --> 00:20:38,410
What are you trying to say?

368
00:20:39,780 --> 00:20:41,280
That just because I don't know
who my parents are,

369
00:20:41,550 --> 00:20:43,210
I might have bad blood?

370
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:46,980
It's the truth, isn't it?

371
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:49,050
For all you know,
your parents could be murderers...

372
00:20:49,790 --> 00:20:50,820
or thieves.

373
00:20:51,390 --> 00:20:53,920
Who knows what kind of filthy blood is...

374
00:20:54,760 --> 00:20:55,790
running through your veins?

375
00:20:57,560 --> 00:20:58,560
Fine.

376
00:20:59,560 --> 00:21:01,000
I don't know who my parents are.

377
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:03,670
But I do know who your mother is.

378
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:05,670
Your mother, Chae Hwa Young,

379
00:21:06,100 --> 00:21:08,740
is a kidnapper, a murderer,
and a despicable monster.

380
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:10,940
So what's worse?

381
00:21:11,640 --> 00:21:15,280
Not knowing who your parents are,
or knowing your mother is a monster?

382
00:21:16,850 --> 00:21:18,180
I think I'd rather not know.

383
00:21:33,330 --> 00:21:34,430
Yes, Manager.

384
00:21:35,230 --> 00:21:36,230
Pardon me?

385
00:21:36,470 --> 00:21:40,540
The Indian tycoon, Chairman Ali,
is coming to our hotel this weekend?

386
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:44,640
She's a very prominent investor
in the business world.

387
00:21:45,110 --> 00:21:49,150
If someone of her stature stays with us,
we'll have to be on top of our game.

388
00:21:51,110 --> 00:21:53,050
Yes, I understand.
Let's hold a meeting right away.

389
00:22:01,120 --> 00:22:02,890
Chairman Ali at our hotel?

390
00:22:04,360 --> 00:22:05,400
Excellent.

391
00:22:06,030 --> 00:22:07,700
I'll have to wrap her around my finger...

392
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:12,040
and get her to invest
in our new Dream Hills project.

393
00:22:14,440 --> 00:22:16,840
You said you found the perfect investor
for our project?

394
00:22:17,170 --> 00:22:20,540
- Who is it?
- Not yet. She's our target.

395
00:22:20,980 --> 00:22:22,610
The Indian tycoon, Chairman Ali.

396
00:22:23,510 --> 00:22:24,920
Chairman Ali...

397
00:22:27,950 --> 00:22:31,290
Right. I see an article
that she's coming to Korea...

398
00:22:31,350 --> 00:22:33,060
to look for investment opportunities.

399
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:36,790
See? This is a sign
that the skies are on our side.

400
00:22:37,230 --> 00:22:39,960
If this works out,
it won't be long before...

401
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:43,500
we're cutting the ribbon on Dream Hills.

402
00:22:43,630 --> 00:22:46,100
I hear she's notoriously picky
about her investments.

403
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:49,910
We'll need a meticulous strategy
to whet her appetite.

404
00:22:50,570 --> 00:22:53,910
If she's going to invest in Dream Hills,
we must paint a very rosy picture for her.

405
00:22:54,040 --> 00:22:56,050
Of course. Absolutely.

406
00:22:56,610 --> 00:22:58,620
Getting someone to part with their money
is never easy.

407
00:22:59,720 --> 00:23:02,890
They said she's arriving this week,
so I'll attend to her myself.

408
00:23:03,150 --> 00:23:05,860
I'll get close to Chairman Ali,
win her over,

409
00:23:06,160 --> 00:23:09,030
and make sure she invests
in our Dream Hills project.

410
00:23:09,330 --> 00:23:11,260
Yes. I'll help as well.

411
00:23:11,830 --> 00:23:13,060
I'll be looking forward to it.

412
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:15,370
About Han Young Ja...

413
00:23:15,470 --> 00:23:19,700
No, never mind.
I shouldn't jinx such a good opportunity.

414
00:23:19,940 --> 00:23:23,170
Jun Ho. How long do you think it'll take
for us to acquire Hills Hotel...

415
00:23:23,470 --> 00:23:27,310
and build our kingdom, Dream Hills?

416
00:23:27,810 --> 00:23:30,680
A month? Six months? A year?

417
00:23:31,110 --> 00:23:33,720
No. A year is too long.

418
00:23:42,860 --> 00:23:43,860
Manager.

419
00:23:44,560 --> 00:23:48,670
Please allow our Dream Project team
to attend to Chairman Ali.

420
00:23:49,470 --> 00:23:50,700
She's a very important person, you know.

421
00:23:56,810 --> 00:23:59,980
Has Chairman Ali's suite
been fully prepared?

422
00:24:00,480 --> 00:24:04,050
We need to pay special attention.
Please double-check the bedding as well.

423
00:24:09,720 --> 00:24:12,590
Team Leader Jin. Regarding Chairman Ali,

424
00:24:13,090 --> 00:24:15,730
I'll handle her arrangements personally.

425
00:24:16,490 --> 00:24:19,160
But you haven't even had
concierge training.

426
00:24:19,630 --> 00:24:21,530
You're a complete novice, so to speak.

427
00:24:22,100 --> 00:24:25,600
- What if you make a mistake?
- What do you mean, a mistake?

428
00:24:25,970 --> 00:24:28,000
I've been in the hotel business
for 30 years.

429
00:24:28,470 --> 00:24:31,510
And I was the CEO.
Do you not know who I am, Team Leader Jin?

430
00:24:32,380 --> 00:24:35,480
- But still...
- I know the concierge's job very well.

431
00:24:35,910 --> 00:24:37,580
Don't worry about that.

432
00:24:37,580 --> 00:24:39,120
Team Leader Jin,
you manage from the inside...

433
00:24:39,120 --> 00:24:40,320
and direct the team on the floor.

434
00:24:40,620 --> 00:24:43,350
Of course I should be the one to attend
to such an important guest.

435
00:24:45,120 --> 00:24:49,090
Remember to place a nice, bright bouquet
in Chairman Ali's room.

436
00:24:49,490 --> 00:24:53,700
She prefers black,
so make sure everything is black.

437
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:55,400
Okay.

438
00:24:55,500 --> 00:25:00,140
Director Ma, Chae Hwa Young says
she'll personally attend to Chairman Ali.

439
00:25:05,180 --> 00:25:07,540
I know I can do a great job.

440
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:09,880
Absolutely not.

441
00:25:10,250 --> 00:25:11,680
We already have a designated concierge
for this,

442
00:25:12,050 --> 00:25:14,920
so how can an employee like Chae Hwa Young
attend to such a distinguished guest?

443
00:25:15,320 --> 00:25:16,620
Don't be ridiculous.

444
00:25:17,720 --> 00:25:18,990
I knew you'd say that.

445
00:25:19,690 --> 00:25:22,030
You just oppose anything I want to do,
don't you?

446
00:25:23,690 --> 00:25:26,300
Director Ma, I'm asking you,
just this once.

447
00:25:26,800 --> 00:25:29,170
I'm desperate. Please?

448
00:25:29,800 --> 00:25:34,040
I'm absolutely confident
I can take great care of her.

449
00:25:34,100 --> 00:25:37,340
Why are you volunteering for menial tasks?
That's so unlike you, Chae Hwa Young.

450
00:25:37,640 --> 00:25:42,210
A concierge's job is to see to every need,
from A to Z,

451
00:25:42,550 --> 00:25:45,950
ensuring they have a comfortable stay
with no inconveniences whatsoever.

452
00:25:46,220 --> 00:25:49,550
Can someone who's always been waited on
do that job well?

453
00:25:50,220 --> 00:25:51,350
I can do it.

454
00:25:52,020 --> 00:25:53,920
Just trust me this once, Director Ma.

455
00:25:56,290 --> 00:25:57,290
Fine.

456
00:25:58,130 --> 00:26:01,060
But if you make even one mistake...

457
00:26:01,230 --> 00:26:03,970
and upset Chairman Ali so much
that she leaves for another hotel,

458
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:06,300
then you, Chae Hwa Young,
will take full responsibility.

459
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:10,070
Of course. I'll take full responsibility.

460
00:26:11,140 --> 00:26:12,410
And how exactly will you do that?

461
00:26:13,610 --> 00:26:14,680
Fine.

462
00:26:15,250 --> 00:26:16,310
I'll submit my resignation.

463
00:26:16,710 --> 00:26:20,020
I'll put my resignation on the line
to handle Chairman Ali myself.

464
00:26:20,650 --> 00:26:22,820
Fine. Then go right ahead.

465
00:26:23,790 --> 00:26:25,290
You know she arrives tomorrow, right?

466
00:26:25,620 --> 00:26:27,260
Yes. Tomorrow.

467
00:26:50,310 --> 00:26:55,250
Welcome to Dream Hotel.
It is a great honor to meet you, Mrs. Ali.

468
00:26:56,120 --> 00:26:58,250
I'm CEO Chae Hwa Young.

469
00:27:08,430 --> 00:27:09,430
Darn it...

470
00:27:19,540 --> 00:27:22,180
Sorry about that. I'm sorry.

471
00:27:36,230 --> 00:27:37,660
How suffocating.

472
00:27:38,400 --> 00:27:40,360
How am I supposed to butter her up?

473
00:27:40,760 --> 00:27:42,970
Who are you trying to butter up?

474
00:27:43,030 --> 00:27:45,640
Chairman Ali understands
every word you're saying.

475
00:27:48,970 --> 00:27:51,040
Let's just start with a slap.

476
00:27:53,640 --> 00:27:54,680
My goodness!

477
00:27:54,940 --> 00:27:56,350
How dare you hit me!

478
00:27:57,910 --> 00:28:00,420
I'm a huge K-drama fan.

479
00:28:01,020 --> 00:28:03,950
What you just said was about me, right?

480
00:28:04,150 --> 00:28:06,490
No, wait, that's not what I meant.

481
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:09,790
The CEO of Dream Hotel is so classless.

482
00:28:12,830 --> 00:28:14,960
Let's go to another hotel.

483
00:28:15,970 --> 00:28:17,100
No, wait...

484
00:28:20,900 --> 00:28:21,910
Darn it...

485
00:28:45,700 --> 00:28:47,100
(The First Man)

486
00:28:47,300 --> 00:28:49,900
Get out of the way.
Chairman Ali is furious.

487
00:28:50,070 --> 00:28:52,970
- Please, forgive me, just this once.
- Get on your knees, now!

488
00:28:53,040 --> 00:28:55,810
I have to keep her here
by all means for Dream Hills.

489
00:28:56,170 --> 00:28:57,840
I really have no idea
what this crest means.

490
00:28:58,370 --> 00:29:00,740
I wonder if it's the same
as the crest on my gold spoon.

491
00:29:00,940 --> 00:29:03,410
They said it was the one thing I had
when I came to the orphanage.

492
00:29:03,650 --> 00:29:05,280
Ma'am, I bought this for you.

493
00:29:06,250 --> 00:29:07,920
Why are you doing this to me?

494
00:29:08,050 --> 00:29:10,490
Her eyes look so familiar.
